## Summary

`app.js` is a 23-line Express app with two GET endpoints (`/health`, `/users`). The attack surface is small, so most OWASP Top 10 categories don't apply (no DB, no auth, no user input, no file I/O, no deserialization). That said, there are still real issues and missing defense-in-depth controls worth fixing before this is used beyond a demo.

