# Security Review: `app.js`

I've read the file in full (22 lines) and both `middleware/` and `routes/` directories are empty. Here's an honest assessment — the surface area is small, so there aren't many exploitable findings, but there are several hardening gaps worth addressing.

## Current code

```js
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});

app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: 'Alice', email: 'alice@example.com' },
    { id: 2, name: 'Bob', email: 'bob@example.com' },
  ]);
});

