## Scope Note

This file is only 23 lines and contains two static GET endpoints with no user input processing, no database, no auth, and no body parsing. That means many classic vulnerabilities (SQLi, XSS in rendered templates, CSRF, deserialization, command injection) **have no attack surface here yet**. I'll flag what's actually exploitable today, what's missing as defensive hygiene, and what to add before this grows.

---

## Findings

