const port = Number(process.env.PORT ?? 3000);
app.listen(port, host, () => console.log(`listening on ${host}:${port}`));
```

Put an HTTPS-terminating reverse proxy in front in production.

---

### 6. No error handler — information disclosure risk (OWASP A05) — **Low today, High once routes throw**

Express's default error handler returns full stack traces in non-production. Add an explicit handler now so it's in place before the first throwing route lands.

```js
